00:03:25.530 --> 00:03:28.440
makes the interior angles on the same side

00:03:28.440 --> 00:03:30.630
less than two right angles,

00:03:30.630 --> 00:03:33.390
the two straight lines,
if produced indefinitely,

00:03:33.390 --> 00:03:34.830
meet on that side,

00:03:34.830 --> 00:03:37.653
on which are the angles less
than the two right angles.

00:03:38.790 --> 00:03:40.020
- What the hell is he talking about?

00:03:40.020 --> 00:03:40.853
That's a postulate?

00:03:40.853 --> 00:03:42.090
Like all of these are,

00:03:42.090 --> 00:03:43.230
you know, half of a sentence,

00:03:43.230 --> 00:03:44.790
and they're all blatantly obvious.

00:03:44.790 --> 00:03:46.950
And then comes five, out of left field,

00:03:46.950 --> 00:03:49.110
and it's like an entire paragraph.

00:03:49.110 --> 00:03:50.282
What is he doing?

00:03:50.282 --> 00:03:51.240
(contemplative music)

00:03:51.240 --> 00:03:53.580
- [Derek] This made
mathematicians suspicious;

00:03:53.580 --> 00:03:56.700
it seemed like Euclid made a mistake.

00:03:56.700 --> 00:03:59.280
Greek philosopher Proclus
thought Postulate 5

00:03:59.280 --> 00:04:02.070
ought even to be struck outta
the postulates altogether,

00:04:02.070 --> 00:04:03.693
for it is a theorem.

00:04:04.560 --> 00:04:05.850
But if it's a theorem,

00:04:05.850 --> 00:04:07.050
we should be able to prove it

00:04:07.050 --> 00:04:08.790
from the first four postulates,

00:04:08.790 --> 00:04:10.920
so that's what many people tried.

00:04:10.920 --> 00:04:13.140
Some, including Ptolemy and Proclus,

00:04:13.140 --> 00:04:16.890
believed they had
succeeded, but they hadn't.

00:04:16.890 --> 00:04:18.750
In fact, all they'd managed to do

00:04:18.750 --> 00:04:22.233
was just restate Postulate
5 in different words.

00:04:23.190 --> 00:04:24.960
Here's one formulation.

00:04:24.960 --> 00:04:28.560
If you have a line, and a
point that is not on that line,

00:04:28.560 --> 00:04:31.470
then there is a single unique line

00:04:31.470 --> 00:04:34.620
which will be parallel to the first line.

00:04:34.620 --> 00:04:35.453
For this reason,

00:04:35.453 --> 00:04:38.790
the fifth postulate is often
called the Parallel postulate.

00:04:38.790 --> 00:04:39.623
(contemplative music)

00:04:39.623 --> 00:04:41.580
When the method of direct proof failed,

00:04:41.580 --> 00:04:45.540
other mathematicians, including
al-Haytham and Omar Khayyam,

00:04:45.540 --> 00:04:49.710
tried a different approach,
proof by contradiction.

00:04:49.710 --> 00:04:51.180
The idea is simple,

00:04:51.180 --> 00:04:53.520
you keep the first four
postulates the same,

00:04:53.520 --> 00:04:55.890
but assume that the
fifth postulate is false.

00:04:55.890 --> 00:04:58.770
Then you use those new
postulates to prove theorems,

00:04:58.770 --> 00:05:00.390
and if that leads to a contradiction,

00:05:00.390 --> 00:05:02.550
for example, true equals false,

00:05:02.550 --> 00:05:05.790
well, then it means your new
fifth postulate must be wrong.

00:05:05.790 --> 00:05:07.500
And, therefore, the only
remaining option would be

00:05:07.500 --> 00:05:10.710
that Euclid's version of the
fifth postulate is correct,

00:05:10.710 --> 00:05:13.650
and you would've proven
the fifth postulate.

00:05:13.650 --> 00:05:14.820
So, what would it look like

00:05:14.820 --> 00:05:16.860
if the fifth postulate were false?

00:05:16.860 --> 00:05:18.030
Well, according to Euclid,

00:05:18.030 --> 00:05:19.830
through a point not on a line,

00:05:19.830 --> 00:05:23.910
there could only be one line
that is parallel to the first.

00:05:23.910 --> 00:05:26.610
One alternative is that
there are no parallel lines

00:05:26.610 --> 00:05:28.890
that you could draw through that point.

00:05:28.890 --> 00:05:29.790
- Well, people tried that,

00:05:29.790 --> 00:05:31.500
and they realized that thin lines

00:05:31.500 --> 00:05:32.790
had to be finite in length.

00:05:32.790 --> 00:05:35.130
And they're like, "Well, that can't be."

00:05:35.130 --> 00:05:36.960
- [Derek] So this option was ruled out,

00:05:36.960 --> 00:05:38.700
it contradicted the second postulate,

00:05:38.700 --> 00:05:42.060
which states that lines can
be extended indefinitely.

00:05:42.060 --> 00:05:43.560
The other alternative

00:05:43.560 --> 00:05:46.140
is that you can draw more
than one parallel line

00:05:46.140 --> 00:05:48.960
through a point not on the first line.

00:05:48.960 --> 00:05:49.793
- So that's what they would do,

00:05:49.793 --> 00:05:51.450
they would assume the
postulate five fails,

00:05:51.450 --> 00:05:52.490
and they're like,

00:05:52.490 --> 00:05:53.828
"This has gotta be wrong.
Where's the contradiction?"

00:05:53.828 --> 00:05:55.329
They couldn't find the contradiction.

00:05:55.329 --> 00:05:56.162
(intense acoustic music)

00:05:56.162 --> 00:05:58.380
- [Derek] So proof by
contradiction also failed.

00:05:58.380 --> 00:06:01.500
In total, mathematicians
spent more than 2,000 years

00:06:01.500 --> 00:06:03.390
trying to prove the fifth postulate,

00:06:03.390 --> 00:06:05.583
but everyone who tried failed.

00:06:07.585 --> 00:06:09.480
(contemplative music)

00:06:09.480 --> 00:06:13.950
Then, around 1820, János
Bolyai, a 17 year old student,

00:06:13.950 --> 00:06:17.670
started spending his days and
nights working on the mystery.

00:06:17.670 --> 00:06:21.157
His father became worried,
and he wrote to his son,

00:06:21.157 --> 00:06:24.150
"You must not attempt this
approach to parallels.

00:06:24.150 --> 00:06:26.250
I know this way to the very end,

00:06:26.250 --> 00:06:28.410
I have traversed this bottomless night,

00:06:28.410 --> 00:06:31.920
which extinguished all
light and joy in my life.

00:06:31.920 --> 00:06:36.390
I intrigue you, leave the
science of parallels alone.

00:06:36.390 --> 00:06:38.337
Learn from my example."

00:06:39.900 --> 00:06:42.750
But the young Bolyai didn't
listen to his father,

00:06:42.750 --> 00:06:46.500
he could not leave the
science of parallels alone.

00:06:46.500 --> 00:06:47.790
After years of work,

00:06:47.790 --> 00:06:50.100
he realized that maybe the fifth postulate

00:06:50.100 --> 00:06:52.470
can't be proven from the other four,

00:06:52.470 --> 00:06:54.903
it could be completely independent.

00:06:56.407 --> 00:06:57.240
(soft music)

00:06:57.240 --> 00:06:58.170
See, according to Euclid,

00:06:58.170 --> 00:07:01.110
you could have only one
parallel line through a point.

00:07:01.110 --> 00:07:02.490
But Bolyai imagined a world

00:07:02.490 --> 00:07:04.770
where there could be more
than one parallel line

00:07:04.770 --> 00:07:06.450
through that point.

00:07:06.450 --> 00:07:07.560
But how?

00:07:07.560 --> 00:07:10.770
Well, who said you needed
to have a flat surface?

00:07:10.770 --> 00:07:12.750
On a surface that is curved like this,

00:07:12.750 --> 00:07:14.520
you can draw more than one line

00:07:14.520 --> 00:07:17.250
that is parallel to the original line.

00:07:17.250 --> 00:07:20.670
But wait a second, those
lines don't look straight.

00:07:20.670 --> 00:07:22.560
Well, what makes straight lines special

00:07:22.560 --> 00:07:25.470
is that they're the shortest
paths between two points.

00:07:25.470 --> 00:07:28.650
On this surface, those
shortest paths just look bent,

00:07:28.650 --> 00:07:31.200
because the surface is curved.

00:07:31.200 --> 00:07:33.150
Here's a more familiar example.

00:07:33.150 --> 00:07:35.460
Airplanes always try to
fly the shortest path

00:07:35.460 --> 00:07:36.570
between two cities,

00:07:36.570 --> 00:07:38.670
they're basically flying
in a straight line,

00:07:38.670 --> 00:07:41.190
but that line doesn't
look straight on a map

00:07:41.190 --> 00:07:43.770
because the surface is curved.

00:07:43.770 --> 00:07:46.110
These shortest paths on curved surfaces

00:07:46.110 --> 00:07:48.660
are called geodesics.

00:07:48.660 --> 00:07:50.940
So, all these lines are straight,

00:07:50.940 --> 00:07:51.990
they just don't look it,

00:07:51.990 --> 00:07:53.700
because the world Bolyai had imagined

00:07:53.700 --> 00:07:55.440
turned out to be curved.

00:07:55.440 --> 00:07:58.173
We now know this as hyperbolic geometry.

00:08:00.630 --> 00:08:03.150
- You know, when I used to
think of the hyperbolic plane,

00:08:03.150 --> 00:08:06.270
I would just imagine
it as one giant saddle.

00:08:06.270 --> 00:08:08.370
But that's not really what it is,

00:08:08.370 --> 00:08:10.170
the hyperbolic plane is much more like

00:08:10.170 --> 00:08:12.450
this piece of crocheting.

00:08:12.450 --> 00:08:15.420
So, it starts out pretty
flat and even in the middle,

00:08:15.420 --> 00:08:17.310
but as you move outwards,

00:08:17.310 --> 00:08:20.310
more and more fabric is created,

00:08:20.310 --> 00:08:24.420
and that would push parallel lines apart.

00:08:24.420 --> 00:08:26.310
And the further and further out you go,

00:08:26.310 --> 00:08:28.890
the amount of fabric grows exponentially,

00:08:28.890 --> 00:08:32.460
and that ends up causing
this crumpling effect.

00:08:32.460 --> 00:08:34.860
So if you really wanna think
about the hyperbolic plane,

00:08:34.860 --> 00:08:36.810
I think you've gotta think about

00:08:36.810 --> 00:08:38.370
saddles, on saddles, on saddles,

00:08:38.370 --> 00:08:41.611
like it's a infinite crumpling mess.

00:08:41.611 --> 00:08:42.444
(soft music)

00:08:42.444 --> 00:08:43.470
- [Derek] But that little piece of crochet

00:08:43.470 --> 00:08:45.600
isn't the full hyperbolic plane.

00:08:45.600 --> 00:08:47.970
To show that, we need to make a map,

00:08:47.970 --> 00:08:52.020
one that fits the entire
plane into a disc.

00:08:52.020 --> 00:08:53.100
To show how this works,

00:08:53.100 --> 00:08:56.190
we're gonna fill the entire
plane with these triangles.

00:08:56.190 --> 00:08:58.410
Starting in the middle,
just as with the crochet,

00:08:58.410 --> 00:09:00.120
things look pretty normal,

00:09:00.120 --> 00:09:02.520
but as you go farther out from the center,

00:09:02.520 --> 00:09:04.170
you get all this extra space,

00:09:04.170 --> 00:09:06.990
so you can fit more and more triangles.

00:09:06.990 --> 00:09:08.730
So they appear smaller,

00:09:08.730 --> 00:09:11.880
but they are actually the same size.

00:09:11.880 --> 00:09:14.040
Now, since the hyperbolic
plane is infinite,

00:09:14.040 --> 00:09:16.320
you can keep adding triangles forever,

00:09:16.320 --> 00:09:18.840
and they all need to fit on the disk.

00:09:18.840 --> 00:09:20.460
So as you get closer to the edge,

00:09:20.460 --> 00:09:24.330
the triangles will appear
smaller, and smaller, and smaller,

00:09:24.330 --> 00:09:26.460
infinitely smaller, never ending,

00:09:26.460 --> 00:09:29.790
and you can never quite reach the edge.

00:09:29.790 --> 00:09:32.580
This is known as the Poincare Disk Model.

00:09:32.580 --> 00:09:34.890
Here, straight lines are arcs of circles

00:09:34.890 --> 00:09:37.650
